article.linkText: Holloway scores 26 to lead Tulane over Fordham 89-81
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Collin Holloway had 26 points in Tulane's 89-81 win against Fordham on Sunday. Holloway also contributed five rebounds and three blocks for the Green Wave (6-1). Jaylen Forbes was 4 of 11 shooting, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 8 for 9 from the line to add 18 points. Kolby King shot 3 of 6 from the field and 8 for 8 from the line to finish with 14 points. Antrell Charlton led the Rams (4-4) in scoring, finishing with 18 points, six rebounds and three steals. Will Richardson added 16 points and two steals for Fordham. Abdou Tsimbila also had 13 points, 14 rebounds and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
